<DIV><FONT face=Arial color=#ff0000><STRONG>United States Time Zones Now 
Included on Telephone Search Results</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial size=2>In our ongoing efforts to improve Accurint, we 
continue to add content and make enhancements to the product to make locating 
people even easier. The telephone number search results now include the 
abbreviation for the Time Zone corresponding to phone number. This additional 
information is helpful for pre-call planning.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial size=2>The nine standard time zones for the United States 
are: Atlantic Standard Time (AST), Eastern Standard Time (EST), Central Standard 
Time (CST), Mountain Standard Time (MST), Pacific Standard Time (PST), Alaskan 
Standard Time (AKST), Hawaii-Aleutian Standard Time (HAST), Samoa standard time 
(UTC-11), Chamorro Standard Time (UTC+10).</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial size=2>From the second Sunday in March through the first 
Sunday in November abbreviations for the areas on Daylight Saving Time will 
change in each time zone change along with Daylight Saving Time. Eastern 
Standard Time (EST) becomes Eastern Daylight Time (EDT), and so forth. Arizona, 
Puerto Rico, Hawaii, U.S. Virgin Islands and American Samoa do not observe 
Daylight Saving Time.</FONT></DIV>
